SIMPLE: myopia
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Myopia
<hw>My*o"pi*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Myope</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Nearsightedness;
shortsightedness; a condition of the eye in which the rays from distant
object are brought to a focus before they reach the retina, and hence
form an indistinct image; while the rays from very near objects are
normally converged so as to produce a distinct image. It is corrected by
the use of a concave lens.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Myopic</ent>⟦br⟧
